            "word_freq(tokens) returns a dict mapping each unique token to its integer occurrence count in the tokens list.",
            "top_n(freq, n) returns exactly n (word, count) pairs as a list of tuples sorted primarily by count descending, secondarily by word ascending (lexicographic) for ties.",
            "summary(s, n) composes tokenize, word_freq, and top_n and returns a single string of 'word:count' entries joined by ',' with no spaces.",
            "top_n returns fewer than n pairs only if the frequency dict contains fewer than n distinct words.",
            "The sort order in top_n is stable with respect to the secondary key: among words with equal count, alphabetically earlier words appear first."
          ],
          "examples": [
